HEADWORD: lepidopteron
<hw>lepidopteron</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An insect that in the adult
state has four wings more or less covered with tiny scales.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lepidopterous insect, lepidopteran.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lepidopterous</ent>⟦br⟧
